GRAPH BACKEND LICENSING (INFORMATIONAL)

`crkg` is a client of external graph databases. It does not bundle,
embed, or statically link any graph database server. Deployers are
responsible for installing, running, and licensing their own graph
backend:

  - Neo4j Community Edition (GPL-3.0) — default backend, client-server
    separation preserves this package's Apache-2.0 posture.
    https://github.com/neo4j/neo4j

  - Memgraph Community Edition (BSL 1.1 with Additional Use Grant) —
    planned optional backend in v0.2+. Source-available, not OSI-approved
    open source; converts to Apache-2.0 four years after each release.
    https://github.com/memgraph/memgraph

